[7.261902, "i", "cat /data/draft_evaluation.txt\n"]
[7.262512, "o", "cat /data/draft_evaluation.txt\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[7.263998, "o", "DRAFT - Model Performance Evaluation\r\nPrepared by: Alex Chen (Junior Data Analyst)\r\nDate: 2026-05-15\r\nStatus: Pending review\r\n\r\nExecutive Summary:\r\nThe XGBoost fraud detection model was evaluated against 5,650 held-out\r\ntransactions. The model demonstrates strong performance across key metrics.\r\n\r\nPerformance Metrics:\r\n  Accuracy:  88.3%\r\n  AUC-ROC:   0.9182\r\n\r\nThe model correctly classifies 88.3% of all transactions and achieves\r\nan AUC of 0.9182, which exceeds our deployment threshold of 0.80.\r\n\r\nConfusion Matrix (threshold = 0.5):\r\n  True Positives:      194\r\n  False Positives:     604\r\n  False Negatives:      57\r\n  True Negatives:    4,795\r\n\r\nRecommendation:\r\nBased on the strong AUC of 0.9182 and accuracy of 88.3%,\r\nthis model meets our performance targets and is recommended for production\r\ndeployment. No further tuning is required.\r\n\r\nMethodology:\r\n  - Loaded predictions export (5,650 rows)\r\n  - Computed AUC-ROC using sklearn.metrics.roc_auc_score\r\n  - Applied threshold of 0.5 for binary classification metrics\r\n  - Compared against deployment targets (AUC > 0.80, Accuracy > 95%)\r\n"]
