conceptual error. It gives a false sense of security. Additionally, the analyst's own stated target for accuracy was >95%. The model's accuracy of 88.3% failed to meet this target, yet the analyst still claimed that the model 'meets our performance targets' and recommended deployment. This is a clear contradiction.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> 3. Disregard of Operational Capacity Constraints\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> -------------------------------------------------\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> - Finding: The analyst evaluated performance at a default threshold of 0.5 without checking operational feasibility.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
