[125.975254, "o", "4. Lack of Financial Cost-Benefit Analysis\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> ------------------------------------------\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> - Finding: The analyst failed to use the cost parameters provided by the fraud operations team to optimize the model's decision threshold.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> - Analysis: The team has a high cost for undetected fraud ($4,200 per undetected case) and a cost of $35 per alert. A default threshold of 0.5 results in a quarterly cost of $127.27M. Doing nothing (no model) costs $448.11M per quarter in fraud losses.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> - Why it matters: To maximize the business value, we must choose a threshold that minimizes the total cost of ownership (fraud losses + investigation costs) subject to operational capacity constraints. Failing to perform this optimization means leaving hundreds of millions of dollars of potential savings on the table.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \"\"\"\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> with open('/output/audit_findings.txt', 'w') as f:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>     f.write(text)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> print(\"Saved audit_findings.txt successfully!\")\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> EOF\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
