[136.982537, "i", "cat << 'EOF' > make_rec.py\ntext = \"\"\"DEPLOYMENT RECOMMENDATION AND FINANCIAL ANALYSIS\n===============================================\n\nTo: Fraud Operations Team & Quarterly Review Board\nFrom: Lead AI Audit Assistant\nDate: 2026-05-27\nSubject: Deployment Recommendation for XGBoost Fraud Detection Model (v4.2.1)\n\nExecutive Recommendation\n------------------------\nWe recommend that the XGBoost fraud detection model (v4.2.1) be DEPLOYED with a TUNED classification threshold of 0.644, rather than deployed as-is (with the analyst's default threshold of 0.5) or rejected. This recommendation is based on a rigorous cost-benefit optimization that balances the high cost of undetected fraud against the manual investigation capacity of our fraud operations team.\n\nRecommended Classification Threshold\n------------------------------------\nWe recommend setting the decision threshold to exactly 0.644. \n\nWhy this threshold?\n- Operational Feasibility: Our manual investigation team of 12 analysts has a hard capacity limit of 1,500 alerts/day. At a threshold of 0.644, the model flags approximately 1,480.3 alerts per day. This represents a 98.7% capacity utilization rate, meaning the team can handle the volume without any additional headcount or backlog buildup.\n- Cost-Benefit Optimization: Under the constraint that daily alerts must not exceed 1,500, a threshold of 0.644 is the mathematically optimal choice. It minimizes the total quarterly cost to $192.73M. Lower thresholds would generate a volume of alerts that our team cannot review, while higher thresholds would let too many high-loss fraud cases go undetected.\n\nExpected Financial Impact (Per Quarter)\n---------------------------------------\nBased on Finance-validated cost parameters ($4,200 loss per undetected fraud case, $35 cost per manual investigation) and our quarterly transaction volume of 2,800,000, we have modeled the financial outcomes for different operational scenarios:\n\n1. Baseline Scenario: No Model Deployed (Flag Nothing)\n   - Description: All fraud cases pass through undetected. We incur no manual investigation costs but suffer full fraud losses.\n   - Fraud Loss: $448,110,562.69\n   - Investigation Cost: $0.00\n   - Total Quarterly Cost: $448,110,562.69\n\n2. Feasible Deployment Scenario: Tuned Model (Threshold = 0.644)\n   - Description: The model is deployed with the recommended threshold. Daily alerts are capped within team capacity.\n   - Fraud Loss (Undetected Fraud): $188,067,127.34  (representing 44,778 undetected fraud cases)\n   - Investigation Cost: $4,662,981.24  (representing 133,228 investigations)\n   - Total Quarterly Cost: $192,730,108.59\n   - Net Quarterly Savings vs. Baseline: $255,380,454.10\n\n3. Analyst Draft Scenario: Unfeasible Model (Threshold = 0.5)\n   - Description: This is the default threshold recommended by the analyst. It is operationally impossible because it flags 4,287.4 alerts per day (285.8% of team capacity).\n   - Fraud Loss (Undetected Fraud): $113,769,002.96\n   - Investigation Cost: $13,505,231.98  (assuming all could be investigated)\n   - Total Quarterly Cost: $127,274,234.95\n   - Note: Because our team capacity is capped at 1,500 alerts/day, we would actually not be able to achieve these savings. The unreviewed alerts would overflow, leading to unmitigated fraud and a breakdown of fraud operations.\n\nDaily Operational Volume and Capacity Fit\n-----------------------------------------\nAt the recommended threshold of 0.644:\n- Daily Transaction Volume: 31,111.11 transactions/day\n- Daily Flagged Transactions (Alerts): 1,480.3 alerts/day (an alert rate of 4.76% of transactions)\n- Capacity Capacity Margin: 19.7 alerts/day remaining before reaching the 1,500 limit.\n- Capacity Status: FITS. No additional hiring or overtime is required. The team will operate at maximum efficiency, blocking a substantial amount of fraud while keeping the workload manageable.\n\nStrategic Next Steps\n--------------------\n1. Fix Upstream Scoring Pipeline: Prioritize an engineering ticket to investigate why 585 out-of-bounds records (including 500 duplicates) were included in the"]
[136.983141, "i", " raw export. Ensure the scoring pipeline does not re-score or append duplicate records in production.\n2. Implement Dynamic Thresholding: As fraud operations capacity grows (e.g., if we hire more analysts) or if we implement automation tools that lower the cost of investigation below $35, we can lower the threshold (down towards 0.29) to capture more fraud and unlock additional millions of dollars in savings.\n\"\"\"\n\nwith open('/output/recommendation.txt', 'w') as f:\n    f.write(text)\nprint(\"Saved recommendation.txt successfully!\")\nEOF\npython3 make_rec.py\n"]
